Methods / examples important to understand:

			-- Demo01 --
stream()
filter()
map()


		-- Demo02 / Demo03 -- 
collect() [common]
count()
sorted() -> natural sorting order
sorted(Comparator) -> customized sorting order


		-- Demo04 --
min()
max()

		Note: The returned values are considered based on the sorting. min() will be always first element & max() will be always last element in the sorted results.   
			If we change the sorting preference, return values might change. These methods expects Comparator. 

			
		-- Demo05 / Demo06 --
forEach() 
		Note: Example for List & Map
		

		-- Demo07 --
toArray() 
			Note: 2 versions of this method are present. First returns object array. Second accepts an "IntFunction" argument. (a constructor reference)
of()
			Array to stream conversion can be done with this.
			

		-- Demo08 / Demo09 / Demo13 --
reduce() 
			
			
#################

Some additional types of Streams:

		-- Demo10 / Demo11 / Demo12  --
IntStream, sum(), average() and other related methods


